For a vocabulary of size V=150,000, the uniform distribution U(i) = 1/V for all i.

Forward KL: KL(P||U) = Σ P(i) * log(P(i) / (1/V)) = Σ P(i) * log(P(i) * V) = Σ P(i) * log(P(i)) + log(V) = -H(P) + log(V)

Backward KL: KL(U||P) = Σ (1/V) * log((1/V) / P(i)) = (1/V) * Σ log(1/(V*P(i))) = -(1/V) * Σ log(V*P(i)) = -(1/V) * Σ (log(V) + log(P(i))) = -log(V) - (1/V) * Σ log(P(i))

So:
- Forward KL = log(V) - H(P) = 10.0
- Backward KL = -log(V) - (1/V) * Σ log(P(i)) = 10.0

